verbose_text: 18 Treatment with saturated hydrogen significantly reduced the activation of p65 signal protein, which is consistent with the findings of a prior report where treatment with H 2 S reduced the expression levels of TNF-alpha, IL-6, IL-10, and monocyte chemoattractant protein-1, as well as the protein levels of p50, p65, and p-p65 in the kidney of rats with chronic renal failure via NF-kappaB signaling.
evidence: hydrogen significantly reduced the activation of p65
